description: Stately and rare, this work of art came to life in 1914. A rigorous restoration allows the artisan details and exceptional craftsman quality to shine. The main floor rooms extend out from the elegant foyer: south-facing living room accommodates languid days; bright sunroom overlooks brick courtyard; dining room for 20; and kitchen which nourishes lively gatherings with room for all. The entire residence is supported by updated systems: new heating & cooling, plumbing, wiring, restoration quality exterior paint, and all brick has been tuckpointed to ensure integrity for 100 years. Nestled on a tranquil street by Volunteer Park, embrace the best of Capitol Hill. Bring your entrepreneurial spirit and envision a thriving business here!
